Help [=[

matrix.new(d1, d2, ... [, iscomplex])
matrix.zeros(d1, d2, ... [, iscomplex])
matrix.ones(d1, d2, ... [, iscomplex])
--------------------------------------

Returns a matrix with dimensions `d1`, `d2`, and so on. If last argument
`iscomplex` is **true**, the returned matrix is _complex_. The entries are
_arbitrary_ (not initialized) when using `new`, initialized to zero when
using `zeros`, and initialized to one when using `ones`.
]=]
